HEADWORD: Rigoll
<hw>Rig"oll</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr.
<ets>regal</ets>.]</ety> <def>A musical instrument formerly in use,
consisting of several sticks bound together, but separated by beads, and
played with a stick with a ball at its end.</def> <au>Moore (Encyc. of
Music.).</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

